# acc-webgui htpasswd — TEMPLATE (commit-safe placeholder).
#
# The real credentials live next to this file as `acc-webgui.htpasswd`
# (gitignored).  This template stays committed so:
#   1. `podman-compose up` finds a file at the bind-mount source even on
#      a fresh checkout (no empty-directory trap that silently breaks
#      htpasswd login).
#   2. New operators have a copy-paste starting point that documents the
#      expected format.
#
# Setup (one-time, on the host that runs `acc-deploy.sh up`):
#
#   1. Copy the template:
#        cp acc-webgui.htpasswd.example acc-webgui.htpasswd
#
#   2. Replace this file's contents with real bcrypt hashes — use
#      `htpasswd -B` (the bcrypt flag is required; SHA / MD5 / crypt
#      lines are skipped with a warning by acc.webgui.auth):
#        htpasswd -B -c acc-webgui.htpasswd alice    # creates the file + alice
#        htpasswd -B    acc-webgui.htpasswd bob      # adds bob
#
#   3. In `.env` at the repo root set:
#        ACC_WEBGUI_AUTH_MODE=htpasswd
#        ACC_WEBGUI_SESSION_SECRET=<32+ random bytes; `openssl rand -hex 32`>
#        ACC_WEBGUI_OPERATOR_USERS=alice                  # comma-separated
#        # (optional override; the compose default points at this file)
#        # ACC_WEBGUI_HTPASSWD_PATH=/app/acc-webgui.htpasswd
#
#   4. `acc-deploy.sh up` (or `podman-compose up -d`).  Edits to the
#      file are picked up on the next login — no restart needed.
#
# Format: one entry per line, `username:bcrypt_hash`.  Comments and
# blank lines are skipped.  See docs/howto-webgui-htpasswd.md for the
# full runbook + troubleshooting table.
#
# The placeholder entry below is a bcrypt of the literal string
# "placeholder-do-not-use".  It exists so the file is non-empty and
# parseable; logging in with it will FAIL because the password isn't
# documented anywhere — that's intentional.
placeholder:$2b$12$0vQ8sKj9w5j4nXp1cQ2YQOH5XjvKkzU/Y4Y3p7s7uYzPq.gK3J6oS
